content.description: Start matched on a slightly positive flake. Pull a series of heel-hooky moves around the corner to an easy topout.
content.location: Just below White Wall. Easiest access parking from CCC lot.

content.description: Sit start with left hand edge and right out in crack.  Stand into side-pull and slap the juggy arete.  Top-out.
Start on the left facing jug. Climb through great underclings and sidepulls to an airy topout. Stays on you the whole time.
content.location: Above "White Wall" in the Swartling Guide

content.description: Start as for Pivot Point and climb the obvious squeeze feature.
content.protection: Several pads and probably a spotter
content.location: See the problem Pivot Point for good directions.

content.description: Start from a crouch with a sloper pinch for the right hand, left on a good sidepull in the face, and a right heel hook.  Move right gaining rail systems, a jug and an easing finish.
content.location: Right at the base of the white wall crag.  Park at ccc parking.  Walk east on road a few minutes to base of small dip and a reduced speed sign that faces east.  Walk uphill crossing a talus field easily visible from road.  The Pivot Point Boulder is in the trees just above the talus field.  The Ogenisis/ young eggs Boulder is just 50 feet west.  Total walk time from ccc parking is about 10 min.

content.description: Start low with hands matched on left facing pinch rail. Powerful left hand move to gain the start hold of Young Eggs.
Stand start with right hand meat hook and left hand on notched area of the arete. A few powerful moves on edges leads to a jug system that trends left to the top out.
content.location:
Young Eggs Boulder. Park at CCC lot and walk east on the road for a few minutes to a reduced speed sign. Hike to the talus field visible from the road. The large roof boulder in the center of the field is the Young Eggs Boulder (it's a bit hidden behind a small grove of trees).

 GPS: 43.412138, -89.706969

content.description: Start matched on low horn used as a heal as for pivot point.  Climb the Boulder.
content.location: Pivot Point Boulder, see the problem Pivot Point for good directions.
